# Manages the session state file (~/.config/wayland-desktop/session_state.json),
# which maps each snapshot entry's tracking_uuid to the live internalId of
# the window that was placed at restore time.
#
# This is the adopted alternative to Qt dynamic properties (setProperty /
# property), which were confirmed unavailable in the KWin JS sandbox on
# 2026-03-21.  See ADR-260321-01.
#
# File format (JSON):
#   {
#     "<tracking_uuid>": {
#       "internalId":     "<kwin internalId UUID>",
#       "app_alias":      "thunderbird",
#       "resource_class": "thunderbird-esr",
#       "desktop":        "Main",
#       "screen":         "main",
#       "placed_at":      "2026-03-21T21:55:00"
#     },
#     ...
#   }
#
# Entries are session-scoped: they are valid only until the next reboot.
# On load, entries from previous boot sessions are pruned automatically
# using /proc/uptime to determine the current session start time.
